values: Title: Dragon Attack Fandom: Live Free or Die Hard Characters: John/Matt Rating: PG Word Count: 17047 words Summary: No. No way. Dragons? Dragons only exist in folklore and a couple of supremely cool video games, and ol' AC has clearly hit his head if he thinks that mythical beings have somehow decimated Times Square. Notes: Written for . I've taken liberties with all aspects of the NYC subway system (hey, I tried to be accurate but those maps are damn confusing and I know there wouldn't be kiosks on the platform level but just work with me here, okay?) I couldn't come up with a better title, either. Dragon Attack on Archive of Our Own If you are inclined to leave a comment, feel free to do so here or at the archive. :) .

We are just starting the SIXTH round over at and we'd love for you to join us! Lands of Magic is a writing and graphics challenge community where you join a team and earn points for your creations. Challenges are generally posted once a week. It has expanded its reach for this new round, so the community is now accepting creative works for any fantasy, horror, sci-fi or superhero fandom! Stop on by and check us out. I'm on Team Summer -- tell 'em Severina sent ya!
Sign up HERE! .

Round TEN is upon us over at -- wow, I've been doing this a looong time -- and it's not too late to join us! If you enjoy writing, making graphics, or compiling fanmixes for any TV based fandom, new or old, you might just have a grand ol' time over at . Join a team, play for points, and have some fun while you're at it!
Drop on by and check it out!

GOALS FOR 2016
 01. Health A. Get back on track with weight loss. I'm not going to set a goal weight at the moment, nor am I going to set a workout goal. Basically at this point my goal is to get back into the right mindset to start -- because without that, it is doomed to failure. So the goal is essentially to update this goal at the 3 month mark with something more definitive. B. See nose specialist again and make a decision about surgery. 02. Writing - Once again my goal is 200K for the year and 14 writing days per month. And I want an UNBROKEN CHAIN. 03. Movies - Relaxing the restrictions here. The whole point of this goal was to encourage myself to finally watch all those movies I SAY I want to see but never get around to actually watching. But clearly 50 movies is too much. So the goal is now 40 movies, but only 25 of those have to be new-to-me. That way when I'm watching Die Hard for the umpteenth time, it still counts and I don't feel that I 'wasted' two hours nor feel guilty for not watching something new! 04. Books - I am upping my goal to 45 books. I have a six-foot bookcase filled with books (some of them double stacked) so an addendum to this is that I must re-read a minimum one shelf of those old favourites during the year. The rest of the books will be new-to-me. 05. Money Jar - Money is still tight, but I want to revive this if I can. So the goal here is to put all the coin in my wallet at the end of each Saturday into a savings jar. It might not add up to much, but it'll be somethin'. 06. Memory Jar -- I loved doing my Happy Memories jar in 2014, and in 2015 things were in such an uproar that seeing it sitting almost empty was simply depressing. But I have faith that things will be better this year, so I will again be starting a Memory Jar. And I also want to get back on track with my friends list! I have not really had time or energy for anything for many weeks, but once I'm done all my updating and caught up on where I need to be for my current commitments, I will get back to reading and commenting on your posts. I hope you are all happy and well! .

It's been a rough year and a particularly rough month, and somehow it is already Christmas Eve. I haven't managed to be on LJ very much this month, but I hope you are all happy and well and have enjoyed/are enjoying your holiday celebrations, whatever they may be! And I wish you all a very...
